The Candidate Nomination period runs July 13th - August 10, 2020 for the November 3, 2020 General Election.
To be eligible for School Board Member nomination, you must meet the following criteria:
18 years of age or older
Citizen of the State
Resident of the Grant School District
Registered Voter
Not legally disqualified from holding civil office

Anyone wishing to apply for candidacy, please contact the Shasta County Registrar of Voters to make an appointment
530-225-5376

Dear Families of incoming Kindergartners:

Girl Scouts is here for you!

Now that your girl is ready to start Kindergarten, she is eligible to join in with our live, virtual pre-K meet-up series where she can try out Girl Scout meetings and have fun. For parents, we are also hosting Virtual Open Houses where you can learn more about Girl Scouts and other ways your girl can get involved now and in the future.

Virtual Parent Information Open Houses

If you are interested in participating or just learning more about Girl Scouts, please visit our ‚ÄúEntering Kindergarten in the Fall‚Äù page on our website at https://www.gsnorcal.org/en/join-us/entering-kindergarten.html where you can register for one of our Virtual Open House sessions and request more information in general.

Virtual Pre-K Meet-Up Series for Girls

To register directly for the Pre-K Meet-Up series for girls, visit https://www.eventbrite.com/e/virtual-pre-k-meet-up-tickets-106011517302.

Stay safe and healthy!

post_text:
Please see message below regarding yearbooks:

Unfortunately, I was notified that our yearbooks will not be delivered before school is out for the summer. They are still being processed at a plant in Tennessee. I was told that they may possibly be shipped in the next 2-3 weeks. I promise to keep you posted on how and when you can pick up your yearbook as soon as I have more information. I apologize for this delay!

Because so many schools are not getting their yearbooks before school gets out, Jostens has launched Yearbook Digital Signing Pages, a one-of-a-kind web experience that provides students with a fun and interactive experience that results in a printable permanent keepsake. It's available and free for all students whether they purchased a yearbook or not.

Check it out at yearbooksigning.jostens.com

Thank you for your understanding!
Mrs. McClung

In an effort to serve our students and their families during the COVID-19 pandemic, Bridges to School Success has created several, free, online groups to help ease tension and make parenting easier during Shelter in Place. On this document, you will see the description of our on-going services and our new FREE opportunities as well as a calendar to help your families select the support that is right for them. If you have questions or need more information, please call Bridges at (530) 225-0350.

post_text:
A message from GRANT ELEMENTARY SCHOOL DISTRICT

Good Sunday Evening Grant Families,

This is Mr. Effa with an important message to all Grant Families. In lieu of constantly changing events with the Coronavirus and recommendations from outside agencies, students will not be reporting to school tomorrow. This means school, preschool and daycare will be closed for the entire day. I will be attending a county wide meeting on Monday to receive updated information on how we will proceed with future school day closures. We will be looking at options for online learning. Plan to receive information Monday evening on the status of school and how we will support students through these circumstances.

Thank you for your patience and understanding as we work together as a Grant Family through yet another unprecedented event.

post_text:
**Free Plants for Fire Recovery**

For anyone who had landscaping that experienced burn related trauma due to the Carr Fire or recent fires and needs replacement trees, shrubs or plants: Shasta College and the Shasta Master Gardeners are having a plant giveaway on March 28th from 1:30 - 3:00pm at the Shasta College Farm. Each family is welcome to come pick up 10 or more plants even if they have received plants from Shasta Master Gardeners and Re-Grow Shasta projects in the past. Volunteers have started plants and trees and have hundreds to be given away. Many of the plants are California native plants and trees.

post_text:
The CEF Annual Art Auction & Appreciation Dinner is right around the corner. We are currently looking for silent auction donations and table sponsors, which are tax deductible. Do you own a business or know of a business that may be interested in donating, please let us know! All donations will be recognized in our monthly newsletter, on the Grant School website, on the Grant School Facebook page, and at the event. Donations can be cash, gift cards, auction items, or services. If you have a unique idea or need help, please contact CEF and we will work out a way to make it happen. Your support is greatly appreciated, and what makes Grant such a wonderful experience for our children. All proceeds from the event are returned to the school in the form of grants for classroom technology, safety & improvements, and educational opportunities. We thank you in advance for your consideration. Go Cougars!!! (For donations and questions, please contact Lori Meadows at meadowsfun5@gmail.com.)

https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B9icZUeghkygZW9TakNiQ0s1WHFadWNmOThXSlBVNy1hQnlZ/view
